        "value": "11 full time staff 8 part- time.Action launching and planning workshops.1 Action review workshop.Regular project coordination.Central/District Project Advisory Committee meetings.Researches and studies on prison conditions(Need and capacity assessment, updating 2008 assessment report of DoPM and research on long-term disabling effect of psychological and mental distress and prison conditions)Mobile health camps.creating  spaces for expression of ideas, opinions and feelings.Radio Jingles for public awareness.Equipment support for database management.Orientation on database management system.Legal and paralegal support.Emergency health, education, livelihood and socio-cultural activities through support groups."
